## 2. Model Policy

The orchestration pattern: an **Opus orchestrator coordinating worker agents**, each in its own context window,
with **read-only advisory/cleanup roles on a cheaper model**. Cost follows criticality.

| Role | Agent | Model | How it is set |
|------|-------|-------|---------------|
| Project Manager / orchestrator | `pm` | **session model (run Opus)** | `/model` or the `model` key in `.claude/settings.json` — **not** agent frontmatter. PM *is* the top-level session, so a frontmatter pin would not apply. Lock the session to Opus via `/model`. |
| Development Engineer | `de` | `{{MODEL_DE}}` | pinned in `de` agent frontmatter |
| Data / QA Analyst | `da` | `{{MODEL_DA}}` | pinned in `da` agent frontmatter |
| Code reviewer (deploy gate) | `code-reviewer` | `{{MODEL_CODE_REVIEWER}}` | pinned in `code-reviewer` agent frontmatter |
| Devil's advocate (adversary) | `devils-advocate` | `{{MODEL_DEVILS_ADVOCATE}}` | pinned in `devils-advocate` agent frontmatter |
| Corpus steward (read-only) | `corpus-steward` | `sonnet` | pinned in agent frontmatter |
| Dead-code cleanup (read-only) | `dead-code-cleanup` | `sonnet` | pinned in agent frontmatter |
| Data reviewer (strict-SoD opt-in) | `data-reviewer` | `claude-opus-4-8` | pinned in agent frontmatter; OFF by default |

**Notes:**
- The reasoning-critical and checked-downstream roles (DE, DA, code-reviewer, devils-advocate) run Opus.
  The read-only sweep roles (corpus-steward, dead-code-cleanup) run Sonnet — the documented sufficient case
  and the real cost saver.
- **Version-pinned intentionally** where the frontmatter names a specific Opus build: re-evaluate the pin on
  the next Opus release rather than letting an alias auto-upgrade.
- **Skills** (`/close-task`, `/log-activity`, `/log-tracker`, `/council`, `/new-doc`, `/audit-corpus`) inherit
  the invoking agent's model — they are markdown injection, not subagent spawns. No skill-level model config.

