## 3. Session Start Protocol

Execute in order at every session start:

1. Read this file (`.claude/CLAUDE.md`) — rules and references.
2. Read `docs/strategy.md` — the GOAL: product + technical strategy, the decision log (the single source of
   truth for "why we do X this way"), risk register. **Mandatory.** Target the `§`-anchors when it is long.
3. Read `docs/architecture.md` — the live system as built TODAY (tech stack, topology, data flow). **Mandatory
   once it exists** (it is created the first time the system has architecture to record). Never write
   architectural assumptions from memory — it is re-audited from live sources, not recalled.
4. Load MCP memory: `search_nodes(<topic>)` for relevant entities (use `read_graph` only when the full graph is
   needed — a targeted search costs a fraction of the tokens).
5. Read `TODO.md` + check the tracker ({{TRACKER}}) — current priorities. **The tracker is the source of truth
   for ticket status**; `TODO.md` is the dependency-ordered roadmap mirror.
6. Read `docs/context_snapshot.md` (if it exists) — last session's state, for a cold resume.
7. Read `docs/INDEX.md` (if it exists) — the autogenerated corpus index; run `affects-lookup` before starting a
   spec that touches governed objects to see what depends on what you are about to change.
8. Read the current task spec (if applicable).

