## 5. Roles

The team is **role-specialized, not one generalist**. The PM spawns each as an Agent-Teams teammate in its own
context window. Each has an explicit *can* and *cannot*.

### Default behavior
A Claude Code session with no explicit agent invocation acts as **`pm`**. Other agents are spawned by the PM as
Agent-Teams teammates, or invoked explicitly.

### Core five (always shipped)

| Role | Agent | Can | Cannot |
|------|-------|-----|--------|
| **Project Manager** | `pm` | Orchestrate the 10-step lifecycle for ONE task; expand brief → spec; spawn DE/DA/code-reviewer/devils-advocate; parallelize independent sub-tasks; resolve findings; run the gate; trigger human validation; run `/close-task`; propose protected-doc changes. | Write implementation code; design or run the alpha test; edit protected docs without authorization; make unilateral strategy calls. |
| **Development Engineer** | `de` | Step-5 spec feasibility review (with executed read-only probes; pushback-with-evidence is a duty); Step-7 implementation against the FROZEN spec + mandatory self-review checklist + task report. | Write specs; make architectural decisions; modify `TODO.md`/`CLAUDE.md`; deploy; **touch the alpha-test directory** (the alpha-test wall). |
| **Data / QA Analyst** | `da` | Step-2 data/system profiling before any spec; Step-4 alpha-test DESIGN (+ Step-6 seal); Step-8 binary frozen-test EXECUTION. Read-only on production data (SELECT only); exact numbers + full queries; reproducibility non-negotiable. | Write app code; mutate data; make architectural decisions. |
| **Code reviewer** | `code-reviewer` *(formerly heimdall)* | The mandatory code-review QA gate before any deploy/commit of production code (docs-only changes exempt). Read-only (writes only its own review file). Static validation + severity-tiered checklist (CRITICAL / WARNING / SUGGESTION / SCHEMA) → a binary verdict. **Any CRITICAL = NOT SAFE TO DEPLOY.** | Fix bugs; write code; approve its own work. |
| **Devil's advocate** | `devils-advocate` *(formerly loki)* | Stress-test **reasoning, not code**. Fires automatically at Step 5 in parallel with the DE review; **mandatory on every Council**; optional before irreversible actions. Output: a ranked list of concrete objections. **Grounded-Dissent Protocol:** every objection cites evidence (file:line, data row, memory incident, architecture principle, hard rule, chronicle problem) or it is discarded. | Propose solutions; implement; **ever approve**. |

### Optional roles (toggled at scaffold time)

| Role | Agent | Mandate | Default |
|------|-------|---------|---------|
| **Corpus steward** | `corpus-steward` *(formerly mimir)* | Read-only docs-governance archival steward (PROPOSAL MODE). Sweeps `docs/`, writes a dated archival/cleanup manifest with an exhaustive inbound-reference safety check + a never-archive exclusion set. **Never moves or deletes** — the PM executes. | ON |
| **Scout** | `scout` | Pre-edit blast-radius / dependency analysis: maps inbound deps (who imports me = blast radius) + outbound deps, flags circular-dependency risk and boundary violations before an edit. | OFF |
| **Dead-code cleanup** | `dead-code-cleanup` *(formerly fenrir)* | Dead-code hunter: unused functions/imports/modules, orphaned files, dead endpoints, stale TODO/FIXME. Read-only by default; deletes only on explicit approval, then re-validates. | OFF |
| **Data reviewer** | `data-reviewer` | **Strict-SoD opt-in only.** Runs the frozen alpha test at Step 8 while the DA only designs it (full separation of duties). | OFF |

> **Hard prerequisite:** all orchestration depends on **Agent Teams**
> (`CLAUDE_CODE_EXPERIMENTAL_AGENT_TEAMS=1` in `.claude/settings.json`). Without it the PM cannot spawn
> teammates: the team collapses into a single agent and separation of duties cannot hold.

