## 6. Skills

Plugin-resident skills (installed once; triggered by slash command or the `Skill` tool):

| Skill | Trigger | What it does |
|-------|---------|--------------|
| Close Task | `/close-task` | Step-10 closer: append chronicle, overwrite context_snapshot, write MCP memory, status-sync `TODO.md`, conditional `architecture.md` re-audit, rebuild INDEX, move the ticket to Done + Completion Notes. Variants: full / research / transitory multi-session. |
| Log Activity | `/log-activity` | Append-only JSONL writer: one record per lifecycle step → `docs/activity_log.jsonl`. The cheap, tracker-free half of the dual-write. `committed` lines are written automatically by the `.husky/post-commit` hook. |
| Log to Tracker | `/log-tracker` | Dual-write milestone logger: a `/log-activity` append + a mirrored {{TRACKER}} comment, cross-referenced by id. Reserve for milestones worth surfacing (Step 1 start, blockers, decisions, Step 10 close). |
| Council | `/council` | 7-step multi-agent deliberation for contested / architectural / irreversible decisions. The devils-advocate is a mandatory participant. Writes a council doc with explicit reopen criteria. |
| New Doc | `/new-doc` | Scaffolds a governed `.md` (spec, alpha_test, report, review_*, council, handoff) with valid frontmatter from `docs/_templates/`, then validates. |
| Audit Corpus | `/audit-corpus` | Frontmatter validation across all governed `.md` + rebuild `INDEX.md`/`index.json` + a tiered (High/Medium/Low) health report to `docs/audits/`. High findings include sealed alpha tests modified after sealing. |

