- **data** → `feat/{{TRACKER_KEY}}-NNN-slug` for code; analysis-only/no-deploy work may use
  `research/{{TRACKER_KEY}}-NNN-slug`. Migrations follow the ordered-file convention in
  `.claude/rules/git-workflow.md`.

**Commit prefixes:** `feat(NN):`, `fix(NN):`, `docs:`, `chore:`, `research(NN):` — conventional commits, per
`.claude/rules/git-workflow.md`.

**Hardcoding rule (non-negotiable):** all credentials, tokens, URLs, connection strings, catalog/warehouse
identifiers, and project keys are read from config files, environment variables, or
`.claude/.local/secrets.env` — **never hardcoded in source.**

**Git hooks (`.husky/`):** `pre-commit` validates frontmatter (`--warn-only`); `post-commit` appends a
`committed` JSONL line automatically; `pre-push` rebuilds the INDEX and blocks the push on drift.

**CI (`.github/workflows/`):** `lint-frontmatter.yml` is mandatory — strict frontmatter validation (no
`--warn-only`) + INDEX-freshness verify on Node 24. It is the always-on, bias-free third review layer on the
PR diff.

