## 12. Connections

How **this** project is wired to the outside world: Git (the repo it runs in), the tracker (where tickets
live), and Databricks (the data warehouse, when the stack is data). Identity only — **every credential lives
in the gitignored `.claude/.local/secrets.env`, never here and never in source** (Hard Rule 7). Mirrored,
secret-free, into `.claude/settings.json` and `corpus.config.mjs`.

### 12.1 Git

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Repo | {{GITHUB_REPO}} |
| Host | {{GIT_HOST}} |
| Working branch | `{{GIT_BRANCH}}` |
| Default branch | `{{GIT_DEFAULT_BRANCH}}` |

- **The framework runs on a working branch, never directly on `{{GIT_DEFAULT_BRANCH}}`.** The rule is
  **1 ticket = 1 branch = 1 PR**: each tracker ticket gets its own branch off `{{GIT_DEFAULT_BRANCH}}`, all
  work for that ticket lands on it, and it merges back through exactly one pull request. One session runs one
  task; a ticket spanning several sessions keeps the same branch until it merges.
- Branch names follow the by-stack convention in §8 (`feat/{{TRACKER_KEY}}-NNN-slug` for code; data adds
  `research/{{TRACKER_KEY}}-NNN-slug` for analysis-only work).
- On `{{GIT_HOST}}`: the PR is the merge unit and the CI gate (`lint-frontmatter.yml`) plus the bias-free
  code-review layer run on its diff. Never force-push, never reset shared history (Hard Rule 8).
- Git identity (`user.name` / `user.email`) must be set — commits and the activity log depend on it.

### 12.2 Tracker

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Tracker | {{TRACKER}} |
| Organization / workspace / site | {{TRACKER_ORG}} |
| Team | {{TRACKER_TEAM}} |
| Project / initiative (where this repo's work connects) | {{TRACKER_PROJECT}} |
| Ticket key / prefix | {{TRACKER_KEY}} |
| Cloud id (Jira only) | {{TRACKER_CLOUD_ID}} |

- This repo's work connects to the tracker at **{{TRACKER_PROJECT}}** under the **{{TRACKER_KEY}}** key — that
  is the scope a branch + PR map back to (1 ticket = 1 branch = 1 PR, §12.1).
- **{{TRACKER}}** is the identity: Linear (workspace + team + project/initiative) or Jira (site/cloud id +
  project key, optionally under an epic). `/log-tracker` and `/close-task` post against it via its MCP.
- Token in `.claude/.local/secrets.env` only (`LINEAR_API_KEY`, or `JIRA_API_TOKEN` + `JIRA_EMAIL`). If
